The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (4th Offense)] and Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (4th Offense)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (4th Offense)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (4th Offense)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Roger Donald Stroede Jr was found guilty of OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (4th Offense)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

11:07 AM Court called 22CF232.  Prosecuting attorney Jordan Lippert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Roger Donald Stroede Jr in court in custody from Columbia County Jail.  Attorney Allison J Borsheim in court for Roger Donald Stroede Jr.  ADA Lippert recited agreement.  Defendant Plead no contest to count 1.   Rights and elements.  Court accepted the no contest plea and found defendant guilty of Count 1; judgment to be entered.  Counts 2 through 8 dismissed.  Sentencing statements.  Court imposed but stayed 360 days in the Columbia County Jail to serve consecutive to any other sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years with conditions of probation to include: to successfully complete OWI Treatment Court Program and follow all rules of Treatment Court, to begin next Monday 08-18-2022; serve 36 days of conditional time in the Columbia County Jail with Huber privileges subject to jail policies to commence forthwith, no good time allowed;  pay fines and costs of $2323; maintain absolute sobriety, meaning not possess or consume alcohol, not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription, not possess any drug paraphernalia; 36 month revocation of license; 36 month ignition interlock; complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations; submit DNA sample;  84 days jail credit given.  Adjourned at 11:40 AM.
